ox": [204.2, 925.4, 827.1, 946.3]}, {"text": "$ 3,400", "bbox": [876.0, 925.4, 943.8, 946.3]}, {"text": "1.7", "bbox": [1018.8, 925.4, 1044.8, 946.3]}, {"text": "Customer relationships . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [204.2, 950.4, 827.1, 971.3]}, {"text": "25,000", "bbox": [886.5, 950.4, 943.8, 971.3]}, {"text": "4.5", "bbox": [1018.8, 950.4, 1044.8, 971.3]}, {"text": "Trademarks . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [204.2, 975.4, 827.1, 996.3]}, {"text": "500", "bbox": [912.5, 975.4, 943.8, 996.3]}, {"text": "2.1", "bbox": [1018.8, 975.4, 1044.8, 996.3]}, {"text": "Total . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [204.2, 1008.8, 827.1, 1029.6]}, {"text": "$28,900", "bbox": [876.0, 1008.8, 943.8, 1029.6]}, {"text": "In determining the purchase price allocation, the Company considered, among other factors, the Company’s", "bbox": [204.2, 1075.3, 1112.4, 1096.2]}, {"text": "intention to use the acquired assets and historical and estimated future demand for Nine Systems services. The", "bbox": [162.5, 1100.3, 1112.5, 1121.2]}, {"text": "fair value of intangible assets was based upon the income approach. The rate used to discount the net cash flows", "bbox": [162.5, 1125.3, 1112.4, 1146.2]}, {"text": "to their present values was based upon a weighted average cost of capital of 18%. The discount rate was", "bbox": [162.5, 1150.3, 1112.5, 1171.2]}, {"text": "determined after consideration of market rates of return on debt and equity capital, the weighted average return", "bbox": [162.5, 1175.3, 1112.4, 1196.2]}, {"text": "on invested capital, and the risk associated with achieving forecasted sales related to the technology and assets", "bbox": [162.5, 1200.3, 1112.4, 1221.2]}, {"text": "acquired from Nine Systems.", "bbox": [162.5, 1225.3, 405.8, 1246.2]}, {"text": "The customer relationships were valued using the income approach. The key assumptions used in valuing", "bbox": [204.2, 1279.4, 1112.4, 1300.2]}, {"text": "the customer relationships were as follows: discount rate of 18%, tax rate of 40% and estimated average", "bbox": [162.5, 1304.4, 1112.4, 1325.2]}, {"text": "economic life of nine years.", "bbox": [162.5, 1329.4, 394.9, 1350.2]}, {"text": "The relief-from-royalty method was used to value the completed technologies acquired from Nine Systems.", "bbox": [204.2, 1383.4, 1112.4, 1404.3]}, {"text": "The relief-from-royalty method estimates the cost savings that accrue to the owner of an intangible asset that", "bbox": [162.5, 1408.4, 1112.4, 1429.3]}, {"text": "would otherwise be required to pay royalties or license fees on revenues earned through the use of the asset. The", "bbox": [162.5, 1433.4, 1112.5, 1454.3]}, {"text": "69", "bbox": [627.1, 1484.1, 647.9, 1504.9]}]}